gbv_data.description: I specialize in treating depression using Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) and mindfulness-based interventions. My goal is to help individuals regain joy and purpose in life by challenging negative thought patterns.
With over a decade of experience, I focus on helping individuals manage major depressive disorder through structured therapy and lifestyle interventions.
I work with individuals experiencing persistent sadness, loss of motivation, and emotional numbness, guiding them toward a path of self-discovery and healing.
I offer a combination of therapy and medication management to help individuals struggling with depression find relief and build resilience.

marriage_data.description: I use CBT and Exposure Response Prevention (ERP) to help individuals manage generalized anxiety disorder, social anxiety, and panic attacks.
My therapy approach focuses on mindfulness, relaxation techniques, and cognitive restructuring to help individuals manage daily anxiety and overwhelming stress.
I integrate hypnotherapy, mindfulness, and breathwork to help clients overcome chronic anxiety and build inner peace.
I specialize in treating anxiety-related disorders, providing personalized therapy to help clients regain confidence and control over their fears.

youth_data.description: I work with individuals experiencing suicidal thoughts and self-harm behaviors, offering compassionate support and evidence-based strategies for emotional regulation.
My work focuses on crisis management and suicide prevention, helping clients find healthy coping mechanisms and a renewed sense of hope.
I provide immediate and long-term support to individuals struggling with self-harm and suicidal ideation, ensuring they feel heard and valued.
I help individuals break free from self-harming behaviors by teaching distress tolerance and self-compassion techniques.
